---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE, MODEL } from '../lib/constants';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Why Vexyn exists: free AI image generation that runs entirely on your device. No account, no queue, no prompt logging — plus the terms that apply to what you make.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">About Vexyn</h1>

    <p class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Vexyn is a free AI image generator that runs entirely in your browser. The model downloads to your
      device once, then every image is produced by your own GPU. No account, no queue, no generation
      limit — and your prompts physically cannot be read by us, because they never leave your machine.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-10">Why this exists</h2>
    <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Every popular AI image site routes your prompt to their servers: it waits in a queue, gets logged,
      counts against a credit balance, and often sits behind a signup wall. We wanted the opposite
      architecture — ship the model <em>to the user</em> and let their hardware do the work. That single
      decision is what makes "free, unlimited, private" an engineering fact rather than a marketing claim
      that erodes later.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-10">How it works</h2>
    <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
      On first use, the page downloads <a href={MODEL.url} class="text-[color:var(--color-brand-400)] hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">{MODEL.id}</a> —
      a distilled Stable Diffusion model that produces an image in a single denoising step, small enough
      to run in a browser. Inference runs through WebGPU via ONNX Runtime Web. The browser caches the
      weights, so later visits skip the download. Disconnect from the internet after loading — it still
      works.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-10">Terms for what you generate</h2>
    <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] leading-relaxed mb-3">
      The model is released under the <a href={MODEL.licenceUrl} class="text-[color:var(--color-brand-400)] hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OpenRAIL++ licence</a>.
      Your images are yours, including for commercial use. The licence carries use restrictions that
      apply to you as a user of this site. You may not use the generator to create content that:
    </p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] mb-6 list-disc pl-5">
      <li>violates any law, or harms or exploits minors in any way;</li>
      <li>creates or spreads verifiably false information with intent to harm others;</li>
      <li>defames, disparages or harasses real people, or impersonates them without consent;</li>
      <li>generates personal identifiable information to harm an individual;</li>
      <li>discriminates against individuals or groups based on protected characteristics;</li>
      <li>provides medical advice or is intended to be relied on in legal, financial or safety-critical decisions.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Because generation happens on your device, enforcement is your responsibility — exactly as it would
      be if you ran the model locally yourself. These restrictions come from the model licence and are
      passed on to you as it requires.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-10">How the site is funded</h2>
    <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Ads. That's it. Because your GPU does the compute, our costs stay near zero no matter how many
      images you make — so there is no premium tier, no credit pack, and no reason to limit you.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-10">Open source</h2>
    <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Vexyn's code is open on <a href={SITE.github} class="text-[color:var(--color-brand-400)] hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>. Audit it, contribute, or fork it.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-10">Contact</h2>
    <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] leading-relaxed">
      Ideas, bug reports, or just hello — open an issue on GitHub or email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`} class="text-[color:var(--color-brand-400)] hover:underline">{SITE.email}</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
